# appliance.env.tmpl — rendered to /opt/vibe/env/appliance.env by lib/secrets.sh.
#
# This file holds Tier 1 inline-editable settings declared by app manifests
# with `ui.appliance: "shared"`. The console Settings page (Phase 8.5
# Workstream C) reads and writes these values via the atomic save flow in
# lib/settings-save.sh; operators rarely edit this file directly.
#
# Pre-existing global secrets — POSTGRES_PASSWORD, JWT_SECRET, ENCRYPTION_KEY,
# REDIS_PASSWORD, CONSOLE_ADMIN_PASSWORD, DUPLICATI_PASSPHRASE — live in
# shared.env, NOT here. Those are container-internal crypto material that
# customers never see, while appliance.env holds operator-facing config that
# customers DO change (email provider, backup destination, AI keys).
#
# Idempotency contract: unlike shared.env (where static lines are emitted
# verbatim from the template), appliance.env preserves operator-set values
# across re-runs. If a key is non-empty in /opt/vibe/env/appliance.env, the
# render keeps that value. Only missing keys (newly added to the template,
# or wiped by --reset-env) take the template default.
#
# This file starts mostly empty. Settings get added as Phase 8.5 Workstream C
# (admin config surface) lands more Tier 1 categories. See
# docs/addenda/admin-config-surface.md §2.1 for the full Tier 1 inventory.

# --- AI ---
# Anthropic API key — read by Claude Code (host support tooling, opt-in via
# bootstrap --with-claude-code) and by per-app AI features whose manifest
# declares ui.appliance: "shared" on this key. Empty default; operator sets
# via the admin Settings page (AI category) or via:
#   sudo bootstrap.sh --with-claude-code --anthropic-api-key=sk-ant-...
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Per-app AI knobs that the Settings page writes when the operator picks a
# non-default value. Left commented so adding them to this template doesn't
# silently change app behavior — vibe-tx-converter / vibe-calculators read
# undefined values via their own env validators (defaults baked in upstream).
# Uncomment and set explicit values only when overriding the upstream default.
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=                # vibe-tx-converter; overrides upstream Claude model pick
# VIBE_AFR_FEED_URL=              # vibe-calculators; IRS AFR feed URL override

# --- Email / SMS (consumed by vibe-connect for magic-link delivery) ---
# Settings page → Email & SMS category writes these when operator configures a
# provider. Left commented so a fresh install behaves identically to today
# (vibe-connect treats absent EMAIL_PROVIDER as "none" via its env validator,
# which disables the client portal until configured — same as the manifest's
# declared default).
# EMAIL_PROVIDER=                 # none | resend | postmark | emailit | smtp
# EMAIL_FROM=                     # noreply@firm.com (must verify with provider)
# RESEND_API_KEY=                 # re_...    (when EMAIL_PROVIDER=resend)
# POSTMARK_SERVER_TOKEN=          # uuid-shape (when EMAIL_PROVIDER=postmark)
# EMAILIT_API_KEY=                # em_...    (when EMAIL_PROVIDER=emailit)
# SMTP_HOST=                      # hostname only (when EMAIL_PROVIDER=smtp)
# SMTP_PORT=                      # 587 for STARTTLS, 465 for implicit TLS
# SMTP_USER=
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
# SMS_PROVIDER=                   # none | twilio | textlink
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=              # (when SMS_PROVIDER=twilio)
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=             # AC... (when SMS_PROVIDER=twilio)
# TEXTLINK_API_URL=               # https://textlinksms.com (default; override for self-hosted)
# TEXTLINK_API_KEY=

# --- Backup destination (consumed by vibe-connect via Duplicati handoff) ---
# Settings page → Backup category. Configuring "none" here matches the
# manifest's declared default; vibe-connect blocks new vault uploads after
# 30 days without a configured destination (see the disabledImpacts hint in
# vibe-connect.json). Operators configuring backups should both: (a) pick a
# value here, AND (b) finish the auth flow in the Duplicati UI on its own
# subdomain — this key is the gate, the actual credentials live in Duplicati.
# BACKUP_DESTINATION_TYPE=        # none | s3 | b2 | sftp | local

# --- Time zone (consumed by vibe-payroll for FLSA workweek calculations) ---
# Settings page → Time & Logging category. Per-app override is also possible
# via the per-app env file when a firm operates in a zone different from the
# host.
# TZ=                             # IANA name, e.g. America/Chicago
